This file lists the licenses of third-party dependencies used by Vigil.
These dependencies are included at compile time via Cargo (Rust's package manager).
Their source code is not modified or vendored — they are linked as published crates.

For the complete dependency tree and transitive dependencies, run:
  cargo license
  cargo about generate

Direct dependencies:

  blake3 (https://crates.io/crates/blake3) — CC0-1.0 OR Apache-2.0 OR Apache-2.0 WITH LLVM-exception
  chrono (https://crates.io/crates/chrono) — MIT OR Apache-2.0
  clap (https://crates.io/crates/clap) — MIT OR Apache-2.0
  crossbeam-channel (https://crates.io/crates/crossbeam-channel) — MIT OR Apache-2.0
  env_logger (https://crates.io/crates/env_logger) — MIT OR Apache-2.0
  glob (https://crates.io/crates/glob) — MIT OR Apache-2.0
  hex (https://crates.io/crates/hex) — MIT OR Apache-2.0
  hmac (https://crates.io/crates/hmac) — MIT OR Apache-2.0
  libc (https://crates.io/crates/libc) — MIT OR Apache-2.0
  log (https://crates.io/crates/log) — MIT OR Apache-2.0
  nix (https://crates.io/crates/nix) — MIT
  parking_lot (https://crates.io/crates/parking_lot) — MIT OR Apache-2.0
  rusqlite (https://crates.io/crates/rusqlite) — MIT
  serde (https://crates.io/crates/serde) — MIT OR Apache-2.0
  serde_json (https://crates.io/crates/serde_json) — MIT OR Apache-2.0
  sha2 (https://crates.io/crates/sha2) — MIT OR Apache-2.0
  thiserror (https://crates.io/crates/thiserror) — MIT OR Apache-2.0
  toml (https://crates.io/crates/toml) — MIT OR Apache-2.0
  uuid (https://crates.io/crates/uuid) — Apache-2.0 OR MIT
  xattr (https://crates.io/crates/xattr) — MIT OR Apache-2.0

All listed dependencies are compatible with GPL-3.0-only.
